      • loadPDF

        public static PDDocument loadPDF(InputStream input)
                          throws IOException
        Parses a PDF. The given input stream is copied to the memory to enable random access to the pdf. Unrestricted main memory will be used for buffering PDF streams.
        Parameters:
        input - stream that contains the document. Don't forget to close it after loading.
        Returns:
        loaded document
        Throws:
        InvalidPasswordException - If the PDF required a non-empty password.
        IOException - In case of a reading or parsing error.

      • loadPDF

        public static PDDocument loadPDF(InputStream input,
                                 MemoryUsageSetting memUsageSetting)
                          throws IOException
        Parses a PDF. Depending on the memory settings parameter the given input stream is either copied to main memory or to a temporary file to enable random access to the pdf.
        Parameters:
        input - stream that contains the document. Don't forget to close it after loading.
        memUsageSetting - defines how memory is used for buffering PDF streams
        Returns:
        loaded document
        Throws:
        InvalidPasswordException - If the PDF required a non-empty password.
        IOException - In case of a reading or parsing error.
